# UI Styling & Design Standards

## Color Palette Consistency
Standardized interactive element colors are defined in `frontend/tailwind.config.js`. Use these semantic classes instead of generic grays for high-interaction lists (notifications, chat, buddy requests).

### Interactive Hover Colors
- **Light Mode:** `hover:bg-interactive-hover` (Equivalent to `blue-100/50`)
- **Dark Mode:** `dark:hover:bg-interactive-hover-dark` (Equivalent to `blue-900/40`)

Usage Example:
```jsx
<div className="p-4 hover:bg-interactive-hover dark:hover:bg-interactive-hover-dark transition-colors">
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

## Notification & Communication Lists
- **Unread State:** Use `bg-blue-50/50` (light) and `dark:bg-blue-900/10` (dark) for unread items.
- **Checkmarks:** Mark-as-read checkmarks should be always visible for unread items (not just on hover) to improve accessibility on mobile.
- **Click Behavior:** Clicking a notification or chat item should automatically mark it as read while navigating to the target.

## Dark Mode Standards
- Always use the `dark:` prefix for all components.
- Backgrounds: Use `dark:bg-gray-800` for cards/containers and `dark:bg-gray-900` for main page backgrounds.
- Text: Use `dark:text-white` for headings and `dark:text-gray-300` or `dark:text-gray-400` for secondary text.
- Borders: Use `dark:border-gray-700` for consistent separation.

## Typography
- Use the `font-display` class (Outfit font) for headings and titles.
- Use the default sans font (DM Sans) for body text and long descriptions.
